Islamabad (AP) - Shugaban Majalisar Dinkin Duniya mai zuwa ya sanar a ranar Lahadi cewa yana jinkirta ziyarar da aka shirya zuwa Pakistan "saboda wasu matsalolin jirgin".
An zabi jami'in diflomasiyyar Turkiyya Volkan Bozkir a matsayin shugaban taron majalisar dinkin duniya karo na 75 a watan jiya kuma an shirya zai isa Islamabad ranar Lahadi.
Amma a wani sakon Twitter, ya ce ziyarar zuwa babban birnin Pakistan za ta jira.
Ministan harkokin wajen Pakistan Shah Mahmood Qureshi ya wallafa a shafinsa na Twitter cewa "Ina fatan maraba da ku zuwa Pakistan nan ba da jimawa ba don ziyarar mai amfani da amfani".
Ranar da ta gabata, wani mai farin ciki Qureshi, yayin sanar da ziyarar, ya yi fatan zai tattauna da Bozkir kan wasu batutuwa, ciki har da Kashmir, wanda ke tsakanin Pakistan da makwabciyar Indiya kuma duka biyu ke ikirarin duka.
Pakistan da Indiya sun yi yaƙe-yaƙe biyu daga cikin yaƙe-yaƙe uku da suka yi a yankin da ake jayayya tun lokacin da suka sami 'yanci daga mulkin Birtaniya a 1947.
Sau da yawa bangarorin biyu suna musayar wuta a Kashmir, suna haifar da asarar sojoji da fararen hula a bangarorin biyu.
Pakistan na son Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta taka rawar da ta kamata wajen warware matsalar Kashmir a karkashin kudurorin ta ta hanyar baiwa mutanen da ke zaune a yankin Himalayan damar yanke shawara ko suna son hadewa da Indiya, da Pakistan ko kuma suna son 'yancin kai.
